value.title: USAGM Chief Fires Trump Allies Over Radio Free Europe And Other Networks
value.excerpt: The acting head of the U.S. Agency for Global Media fired the presidents and boards over three not-for-profit international networks who were appointed by an ally of former President Trump.

value.title: New York Times: Trump and DOJ attorney had plan to replace his acting AG and undo Georgia election result
value.excerpt: Justice Department lawyer Jeffrey Clark nearly convinced then-President Donald Trump to remove then-acting Attorney General Jeffrey Rosen and use the Department of Justice to undo Georgia's election results, The New York Times reported Friday.

value.title: Biden says we need to act 'decisively and boldly'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said on Friday the U.S. economic crisis was deepening and that the government needs to take major action now to help struggling Americans.

value.title: Birx: I always considered quitting Trump's White House Covid task force
value.excerpt: Dr. Deborah Birx "always" considered quitting then-President Donald Trump's White House coronavirus task force and was troubled by colleagues' perceptions that she had become political, she said in an interview clip released Friday.

value.title: Rep. Ilhan Omar calls on Biden to back 'recurring cash payments' until economy recovers
value.excerpt: Omar and other progressives have argued that Biden’s proposal does not go far enough to address the current financial crisis.

value.title: Group of Democratic lawmakers urge Biden to commute the sentences of death row prisoners
value.excerpt: Democratic Reps. Ayanna Pressley of Massachusetts and Cori Bush of Missouri on Friday led a group of 35 lawmakers in urging President Joe Biden to commute the sentences of all federal prisoners on death row.

value.title: Biden plans to sign executive orders boosting workers' rights and pushing for a $15 minimum wage for federal staff
value.excerpt: Biden is set to sign an order on Friday ensuring that people can still claim unemployment benefits if they turn down a job because of COVID-19 risks.

value.title: Biden says 'nothing we can do' to change pandemic 'trajectory' in coming months
value.excerpt: Biden addressed his administration’s response efforts during a press briefing on two executive orders meant to provide food assistance to low-income families and protect workers’ rights during the pandemic.

value.title: In first lawsuit against Biden administration, Texas AG Paxton challenges deportation freeze
value.excerpt: Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton asked a federal judge to block a new Biden administration policy that pauses most deportations for the next 100 days.

value.title: Ari Fleischer: 'Big government is back' under Biden
value.excerpt: President Biden's approach to tackling the economic crisis brought about by the coronavirus pandemic shows that "big government is back" in Washington, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer said Friday.

value.title: Reince Priebus: 'Tough time for the Republican Party’ but Biden's actions easy to unite against
value.excerpt: Former White House Chief of Staff Reince Priebus told "America’s Newsroom" Friday that it’s a "tough time for the Republican Party" since President Biden was sworn in, but Biden's actions may make it easier for the party to unite.

value.title: Biden suggests delayed impeachment timeline may be 'better'
value.excerpt: Biden suggested having more time to get his Cabinet nominees confirmed may help jumpstart his policy agenda.

value.title: Alejandro Mayorkas: What to know about Biden's DHS pick
value.excerpt: President Biden has nominated Alejandro Mayorkas to be the next secretary of the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), who will take a key role in the closely watched area of immigration policy.

value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi plans to send the article of impeachment against Donald Trump to the Senate on Monday.

value.title: Fauci says lack of candor from Trump administration 'very likely' cost lives
value.excerpt: Dr. Anthony Fauci said Friday that the lack of truthfulness from the Trump administration regarding the Covid-19 pandemic "very likely" cost American lives.

value.title: Trump hires South Carolina lawyer Bowers for impeachment defense
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump has hired South Carolina-based lawyer Butch Bowers to represent him in his Senate impeachment trial over a charge that he incited insurrection, a source familiar with the matter said on Thursday.

value.title: Gingrich: Dems 'methodically trying to destroy conservatism' with Biden as 'pleasant cover'
value.excerpt: President Biden's "radical" inner circle is working to "destroy" the legacy of President Trump, former House Speaker Newt Gingrich warned on "Hannity" Thursday.

value.title: Biden proposes extending nuclear arms treaty with Russia for 5 years
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has proposed extending a nuclear arms treaty with Russia before it expires next month, White House press secretary Jen Psaki said during a Thursday press conference.

value.title: McConnell proposes delaying impeachment trial until February so Trump team can prepare
value.excerpt: The timing of former President Donald Trump's Senate impeachment trial is still unsettled while Senate leaders haggle over how a power-sharing agreement will govern a 50-50 Senate.

value.title: Obama praises Biden's executive order blitz: 'This is a time for boldness'
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama praised President Biden on Thursday for enacting a sweeping slate of executive orders within hours of his inauguration as president.

value.title: NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg says ‘need to rebuild trust’ after Trump
value.excerpt: After four long years of Donald Trump’s attacks on NATO, Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg said Thursday that the defense alliance had survived the challenge — and that he looked forward to rebuilding the transatlantic relationship with President Biden.
